  "text": "CD26 is a cell surface glycoprotein with dipeptidyl peptidase IV activity in its extracellular domain and is a T cell activation molecule, playing roles in T cell costimulation and signal transduction processes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It is also highly expressed on MM, but not in benign mesothelial tissue, and implicated in tumour growth and metastases (Inamoto et al., 2007) . A humanised anti-CD26 antibody was shown to lyse MM cell lines and also prolong survival in a mouse model of MM (Inamoto et al., 2007) .",
